{
  "stem": "24259.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And during the times my father would go out into the woods and meet up with other people hiding, that they would find out about various people and so on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Another incident that comes to mind was that, during one of these forages into the woods that my father went out, he met up with the parents of a young lady who kind of comes into our lives after being liberated.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They-- they had told him that they had given their daughter, who was approximately the same age as I was-- about eight months younger, actually-- they had given her away to a Polish family.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And shortly thereafter, my father found out that the parents were killed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after we were liberated, my father remembered this incident.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he went and took the girl back, with a great deal of resistance from the Polish family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my father, I'm told, had to get the-- the Russian soldiers to come with him to help him take her back from the Polish family.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And later on, she-- she was with us right through the period from the time that the Russians liberated us through the time that we spent in a DP camp in Germany.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they actually went and adopted her during the time that we were in a DP camp, as-- as their child, or my sister.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And unfortunately-- or fortunately, whichever way you look at it-- she had a-- an aunt in Israel-- Palestine at that time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And somehow, my parents corresponded with the aunt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And the aunt found out that we had her, and she insisted that she come live with her in Israel.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
